<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-100-097 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 049 205</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computerworld  July 29 1991 v25 n30 p74(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Hot search for telecom whizzes: growing technology makes it hardto find qualified telecom employees. (includes related article onthe telecommunications industry in transition)</TITLE><AUTHOR>LaPlante, Alice.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Information systems (IS) professionals with telecommunicationsexpertise are in demand even though many IS departments aredownsizing or reducing staff.andP;  The reason for the growthopportunities is that telecommunications has been identified as acritical component to the success of corporations andorganizations.andP;  Industry experts indicate that firms are willingto offer higher compensation to locate IS professionals withtelecommunications experience.andP;  Expertise in local area and widearea networks, high-speed communications links and financialadministration is in particular demand.andP;  Also, IS professionalswith international telecommunications experience are appealingbecause many corporations are expanding operations to Asia andWestern Europe.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     TelecommunicationsEmployment OpportunityGrowthInformation systemsInternational Trade.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>